Sentencas: Performance of Ca-doped strontium ferrite-molybdate Sr2-xCaxFe1.5Mo0.5O6- (x=0, 0.05, 0.15, 0.3, 0.5) has been studied under reducing conditions.
Titulo: Functional properties and electrochemical performance of Ca-doped Sr2-xCaxFe1.5Mo0.5O6- as anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thermogravimetry (TG) analysis in 5% H-2/Ar and DSC measurements in high-purity argon demonstrated that the compositions are highly stable and there are no phase transitions.
Titulo: Functional properties and electrochemical performance of Ca-doped Sr2-xCaxFe1.5Mo0.5O6- as anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The best electrochemical and electrical performances of about 0.12cm(2) and 33S/cm at 800 degrees C in wet hydrogen, respectively, were obtained for the Sr1.85Ca0.15Fe1.5Mo0.5O6- anode.
Titulo: Functional properties and electrochemical performance of Ca-doped Sr2-xCaxFe1.5Mo0.5O6- as anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The EIS spectra were analyzed by means of distribution relaxation times and non-linear least squares methods, which made it possible to determine the behavior of the rate-limiting steps of hydrogen oxidation.
Titulo: Functional properties and electrochemical performance of Ca-doped Sr2-xCaxFe1.5Mo0.5O6- as anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) of planar design with the 1.5mm LaGaO3-based supporting electrolyte, with the Sr1.85Ca0.15Fe1.5Mo0.5O6- symmetrical electrodes and with the Sr2-xCaxFe1.5Mo0.5O6- (x=0.15 and 0.3) anode and the 70wt% Pr0.9Y0.1BaCo2O6-+30wt% SDC cathode have been studied.
Titulo: Functional properties and electrochemical performance of Ca-doped Sr2-xCaxFe1.5Mo0.5O6- as anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The obtained results demonstrated a low anode overvoltage, which was about 0.12V at 1A/cm(2) and 800 degrees C in wet hydrogen.
Titulo: Functional properties and electrochemical performance of Ca-doped Sr2-xCaxFe1.5Mo0.5O6- as anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of SOFC with the Sr1.85Ca0.15Fe1.5Mo0.5O6- anode and cobaltite cathode was about 0.18W/cm(2) at 800 degrees C under air/wet hydrogen conditions.
Titulo: Functional properties and electrochemical performance of Ca-doped Sr2-xCaxFe1.5Mo0.5O6- as anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The obtained results elucidate that Sr1.85Ca0.15Fe1.5Mo0.5O6- is a promising anode for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Functional properties and electrochemical performance of Ca-doped Sr2-xCaxFe1.5Mo0.5O6- as anode for solid oxide fuel cells
